::DarkMouse::

She heard something in the trees and transformed into bot mode.  She 
reached down and drew her gun. She held the rat close to her body and 
ran behind a thick tree.  She watched and waited.  Nothing happened.  
She breathed a sigh of relief.  She hadn't thought that running for 
your life would make a bot paranoid.

She continued walking, ducking behind trees, listening for all 
noises, sniffing the air.  She was getting very paranoid.
